messages.content: What additional samplers are included in ComfyUI-Extra-Samplers?
The currently included extra samplers are RES, DPMPP Dual SDE, Clyb 4M SDE, TTM, and LCM Custom Noise.
Can you describe the RES sampler?
RES is a sampler that is somewhat naively momentumized and modified, with thanks to Kat and Birch-San for the source implementation.
What sets the DPMPP Dual SDE apart from other samplers?
DPMPP Dual SDE is a somewhat naively momentumized sampler that includes an added SDE, similar to how 3M samples.
Who is responsible for the Clyb 4M SDE?
The Clyb 4M SDE is a modified DPMPP 3M SDE with an added SDE, and was egotisticalized by the author.
Can you mention the acknowledgments for the TTM sampler?
Acknowledgment for the TTM sampler is given to Kat and Birch-San for the source implementation.
What does LCM Custom Noise allow?
LCM Custom Noise offers support for different types of noise other than generic gaussian noise.
What K-Sampling nodes are included in ComfyUI-Extra-Samplers?
The currently included extra K-Sampling nodes are SamplerCustomNoise, SamplerCustomNoiseDuo, and SamplerCustomModelMixtureDuo.
What noise types are supported by SamplerCustomNoise?
SamplerCustomNoise supports custom noises other than gaussian noise for init noise.
What additional feature does SamplerCustomNoiseDuo provide over SamplerCustomNoise?
SamplerCustomNoiseDuo provides a High-res fix for simplicity.
Can you describe how SamplerCustomModelMixtureDuo works?
SamplerCustomModelMixtureDuo samples with custom noises and switches between model1 and model2 every step.
What should be done if vram errors are encountered while using SamplerCustomModelMixtureDuo?
If encountering vram errors, try adding or removing `--disable-smart-memory` when launching ComfyUI.
